  <span id="freeText8652833319074607457" style="display:none">Had to agree with some other reviewers with the opinion that this book needed some serious editing. Little things, and also the entire chapter on the Civil War. Although it was useful to know the historical motivation behind the rebel ex-pats settling in Mexico, a few paragraphs could have done it. I went to Mexico and was hoping for a better overview of the country and culture, which as I recall I got more of 50 years ago when I moved to Hawaii and read his novel Hawaii, but this was more of a microcosm. Of course Hawaii is a smaller place than Mexico. But it was engaging and informative.</span>
